Apoplexy! I tried to burst open the door; but it stubbornly resisted. Running 
down stairs, I quickly stated my suspicions to the first person I met—the 
chamber-maid. “La! la!” she cried, “I thought something must be the 
matter. I went to make the bed after breakfast, and the door was locked; and 
not a mouse to be heard; and it’s been just so silent ever since. But I 
